meta {
  name: Apply Leave
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/hr/leave/requests
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Cookie: auth_token={{authToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "leave_type_name": "{{leaveTypeName}}",
    "start_date": "2026-08-10",
    "end_date": "2026-08-11",
    "start_half": "full",
    "end_half": "full",
    "reason": "Family function"
  }
}

docs {
  Creates the request's approver chain by walking hr.reporting_lines upward from the
  requester (see resolveApprovers / buildApproverChain), effective as of today. This tree
  is independent of the LMS lead-assignment hierarchy (iam.vw_user_team_members /
  iam.users.manager_id) — a rep's LMS lead/manager has no bearing on who approves their
  leave. iam.users.manager_id only seeded the initial hr.reporting_lines rows via backfill.

  If the requester has no resolvable HR reporting line, level 1 falls back to a
  deterministic org_admin/hr_admin for the org.
}
